name: Hobart Hills Hide Out
description:
Retreat to this unique and tranquil cabin with cosy indoor fire place on 11 hectares in the hills of Hobart.

Conforming to solar energy principles, the cabin is a hand - crafted masterpiece designed by renowned environmental architect Steven Sainsbury constructed with Tasmanian Celery Top Pine and stone.

Private cleared land and native trees to walk amongst with a creek and dam on the property.

25 mins to Hobart, 25 mins to the Huon Valley and 15 mins to Kingston Beach.

A perfect retreat
neighborhood_overview: Situated between Hobart and the Huon Valley. 25 minutes one way to Hobart, 25 minutes the other way to Cygnet I the Huon Valley. 15 minutes to Kingston Beach. 10 minutes to the famous Longley International hotel for bistro meals and live music.
